{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \outlinelevel1 \b \fs32 How to Install\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 To install Mantrika Tools, you must have the {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://reapack.com/"}}{\fldrslt{\ul
ReaPack
}}}
 extension installed in your REAPER.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li360 \fi-360 1.\tx360\tab Open REAPER.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li360 \fi-360 2.\tx360\tab Go to the main menu and select: {\f1 Extensions} > {\f1 ReaPack} > {\f1 Import repositories...}.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li360 \fi-360 3.\tx360\tab In the pop-up window, paste the following URL into the address field:\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li360 \fi0 \f1 https://github.com/qhtchestnut/Mantrika-Tools-Release/raw/master/index.xml\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li360 \fi-360 4.\tx360\tab Click {\f1 OK}. ReaPack will synchronize with the repository.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li360 \fi-360 5.\tx360\tab You will be prompted to install the {\f1 Mantrika Tools} package. Click {\f1 Apply} or {\f1 OK} to proceed with the installation.\sa180\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \outlinelevel1 \b \fs32 Usage\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 After a successful installation, it's recommended to restart REAPER.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 You can then find the tools provided by this extension in the {\f1 Extensions} menu, or by searching for their actions in the Action List.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \outlinelevel1 \b \fs32 Support and Feedback\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 If you encounter any bugs, have a feature request, or need support, please feel free to:\par}
